'''Nkosinathi Emmanuel Sibisi''' (born 22 September 1995) is a South African [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[South African Premier Division]] side [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]], who is currently their club captain, and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|nkosinathi-sibisi/441795|accessdate=9 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.goldenarrowsfc.com/1st-team/nkosinathi-sibisi/ |title=Nkosinathi Sibisi |access-date=31 July 2020 |publisher=Orlando Pirates F.C. }}</ref>

==International career==
He made his debut for [[South Africa national soccer team]] on 10 June 2021 in a friendly against [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=602891|title=South Africa v Uganda game report|date=10 June 2021|accessdate=11 August 2021}}</ref> In 2022, he appeared in three international friendlies.<ref>{{NFT player|82955}}</ref> On the 10th of February 2024 he won AFCON 23 bronze medal with his national team South Africa

On 1 December 2025, Sibisi was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

